<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-22T19:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-22T19:36:00-05:00" n="997" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d997">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/242.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-22T18:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s March 21, 11 a.m., and my March 22, 11 a.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d997fn1">See Mar. 22, 12 noon.</note> The committee of the
                            American colony desire me to add to the order 1,000 field-service belts
                            and to increase the number of rifle cartridges from 250,000 to
                            1,000,000.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>